UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2045
1 AN ACT relating to appropriations.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 Section 1. KRS 45.760 is amended to read as follows:
4 The provisions of any other law notwithstanding:
5 (1) During any biennium the amount allotted, from all sources, for expenditure on any
6 project in the state capital construction program for that biennium shall not exceed
7 the estimated cost of the project during that biennium, as shown in any branch
8 budget bill enacted by the General Assembly, except as provided in this section and
9 KRS 45.770 and 45.780.
10 (2) When the General Assembly disapproves a capital project or item of equipment that
11 was previously approved, it shall be eliminated as a capital project or major item of
12 equipment in the Capital Projects Program. General fund moneys appropriated for
13 that project or item of equipment but not allotted, and general fund moneys allotted
14 but not expended to the project or equipment account, shall be transferred to the
15 capital construction and equipment purchase contingency account in the capital
16 construction fund. Agency or federal funds for a disapproved project or item, that
17 have been appropriated but unallotted or allotted but unexpended, shall be returned
18 to the appropriate agency fund. Road fund moneys for a disapproved project or item
19 that have been appropriated but unallotted or allotted but unexpended, shall be
20 returned to the Road Fund Surplus Account.
21 (3) Capital projects and major items of equipment disapproved under subsection (2) of
22 this section shall be terminated.
23 (4) During any biennium, the amount allotted from all sources for expenditure for the
24 purchase of any major item of equipment shall not exceed the estimated cost of the
25 item as shown in any branch budget bill enacted by the General Assembly and
26 authorizing the purchase, except as provided in subsections (5) and (6) of this
27 section and in KRS 45.770 and 45.780.
