1 (5) A major item of equipment to be used for medical, scientific, or research purposes,
2 excluding computer equipment and aircraft, may be authorized even though it is not
3 specifically listed in any branch budget bill enacted for the current biennium,
4 subject to the following conditions and procedures:
5 (a) Moneys specifically budgeted and appropriated by the General Assembly for
6 another purpose shall not be reallotted for expenditure on the item; moneys
7 utilized shall not jeopardize any existing program and shall not require the use
8 of any current general funds specifically dedicated to existing programs;
9 (b) Funds are available for the purchase and the method of financing the purchase
10 will not require an additional appropriation of state funds to acquire the item;
11 and
12 (c) The purchasing agency shall, within thirty (30) days after making the
13 purchase, report the purchase to the Capital Projects and Bond Oversight
14 Committee. The report shall include a description of the item, the purpose for
15 which it will be used, the necessity for the purchase, and the amount expended
16 for the purchase from each source of funds used.
17 (6) Moneys from any source may be transferred to the allotment account of any capital
18 project authorized by the General Assembly under this section, subject to the
19 following conditions and procedures:
20 (a) The total amount transferred shall not exceed fifteen percent (15%) of the
21 amount authorized by the General Assembly unless:
22 1. The source of funds is private or federal; or
23 2. An unforeseen decision by a federal or state court or regulatory agency
24 requires the transfer.
25 (b) Moneys specifically budgeted and appropriated by the General Assembly for
26 another purpose shall not be allotted or reallotted for expenditure on the
27 capital project.
