UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2045
1 (c) Moneys utilized shall not jeopardize any existing program and shall not
2 require the use of any current general funds specifically dedicated to existing
3 programs.
4 (d) The relevant entity head, or his or her designee, shall submit the capital
5 project to the Capital Projects and Bond Oversight Committee at least
6 fourteen (14) days prior to the committee meeting. The submission shall
7 include a written certification to the committee that the transfer, in excess of
8 fifteen percent (15%) of the amount authorized by the General Assembly, is:
9 1. Paid for out of private or federal funds; or
10 2. Required by an unforeseen decision by a federal or state court or
11 regulatory agency; and
12 3. Not allotted or reallotted from moneys specifically budgeted and
13 appropriated by the General Assembly for another purpose; and
14 4. Not jeopardizing any existing program and not requiring the use of any
15 current general funds specifically dedicated to existing programs.
16 (e) If a capital project is financed with road funds, the cost overruns or scope
17 increases shall be paid out of the highway contingency account established
18 pursuant to KRS 45.247.
19 (7) A capital construction project or a major item of equipment may be authorized even
20 though it is not specifically listed in any branch budget bill, subject to the following
21 conditions and procedures:
22 (a) Fifty percent (50%) or more of the actual cost shall be funded by federal or
23 private funds, and fifty percent (50%) or less of the actual cost shall be funded
24 by moneys appropriated to the capital construction and equipment purchase
25 contingency account or, if the purpose of the project or equipment is to reduce
26 energy costs, the relevant entity head certifies projected energy cost savings
27 associated with the project or equipment are reasonable and sufficient to
