UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2045
1 produce an aggregate simple payback period, as defined by KRS 56.770, of
2 five (5) years or less;
3 (b) Moneys specifically budgeted and appropriated by the General Assembly for
4 another purpose shall not be allotted or reallotted for expenditure on the
5 project or major item of equipment; moneys utilized shall not jeopardize any
6 existing program and shall not require the use of any current general funds
7 specifically dedicated to existing programs; and
8 (c) The relevant entity head, or his or her designee, shall submit the project or
9 major item of equipment to the committee for review as provided by KRS
10 45.800.
11 (8) The capital construction and equipment purchase contingency fund may be used to
12 advance funds to projects authorized to be financed by bonds, to finance feasibility
13 studies for projects which may be contemplated for future funding, or to audit the
14 capital projects program when authorized by the General Assembly.
15 (9) On or before October 1, each branch of government shall submit to the committee
16 the following information:
17 (a) A complete list and summary description of every capital construction project
18 and major item of equipment not completed as of June 30 of the prior fiscal
19 year; and
20 (b) For each project and major item of equipment, as of July 1, of the current
21 fiscal year:
22 1. The project phase;
23 2. The project account number, project name, and any other term employed
24 to identify the project or major item of equipment;
25 3. The available balance in the project or major item of equipment account,
26 and any sums considered available for that project or major item of
27 equipment;
