1 4. A statement of the transfers of funds to or from the project or major item
2 of equipment account; and, any account to which transfers from each
3 project or major item of equipment has been made;
4 5. The year in which the project or major item of equipment was approved,
5 with specific reference to the legislation by which the project or item
6 was approved;
7 6. Total expenditure on the project or major item of equipment;
8 7. The current estimated completion cost, including the amount required
9 for annual inflation; and
10 8. A statement that additional funds for the completion of the project or
11 major item of equipment are or are not required; and, if required, why
12 sufficient funds for completion are not available; and
13 (c) The balance in the appropriated, but unallotted account; and the balance in
14 any account, however designated, that contains appropriated, but unallotted
15 funds for capital construction.
16 (10) When the General Assembly authorizes a capital construction item in the capital
17 construction section of a branch budget bill, the entity head charged with executing
18 the branch budget shall construct the capital construction item according to the
19 requirements set forth in the branch budget bill, supporting documentation
20 considered by the General Assembly, and branch budget records. The entity head
21 shall not deviate from these requirements with regard to:
22 (a) Purpose or location to the extent that the capital construction item no longer
23 meets the identified needs; or
24 (b) Configuration for reasons other than practical accommodation to the
25 construction site or specific program to be accommodated within that capital
26 construction item.
